task.summary: Default task
Commiting after changes with IntelliJ

Planet Class is pretty much done. It provides the attributes and methods for Planet objects. I created a separate class named PlanetMaker that will contain all the String Messages for Name, explore message, scan message, and arrival message as arrays. It will also contain all the predefined Planet objects added into a planetArrayList which is added at the top of GameController. Only attribute that is allowed to be modified is if the boolean of whether or not a planet has been explored. I also changed a few attributes of planets. Instead of having booleans for whether it is a gasplanet, bossplanet, or specialPlanet(Created a doc file with descriptions) I created another int flag notation since there was no case where two of these existed at the same time.

UPDATE: 11/7/2015 Planet Class, Puzzle Class, and Dice Class are all completed. PlanetMaker Class and PuzzleMaker Class are structurally completed. Just need to insert actually message descriptions. However, all my classes should be testable. I created a few test Puzzles that are integrated to three Planets as well. I created another class called Dice which the constructor takes in percent chance of hitting with a method called roll that return a Boolean. Fixed GameController items that were related to puzzle or planet objects. Added some notes to both Captain and Enemy where they should both extend Persona. . . Also Enemy and Captain both have names so that should also go into Persona, instead of having setCaptain name and setEnemy Name.
UPDATE: 11/9/2015 Kenny Cauthen Minor Changes. Added boolean flag for if planet has been explored to Planet class. Some minor edits to clean up code in Puzzle and PuzzleMaker Class.
UPDATE: 11/9/2015 Kenny Cauthen Minor Changes. Sample Menu Item for Starter screen at bottom of GamController

UPDATE: 11/14/2015 Kenny Cauthen Changes made to gamecontroller 2 and Game. Game load method now a contructor. Save game method takes in Path String for save. For loading, I think Game object should only be used to load into all the attributes to game controller. I think Game should save from gameController's thisGame object. Initial menu system implemented and works. Fixed my classes where they were pointing to null. Fixed puzzleArrayListGenerator algorithm. Removed all static reference and fixed static exceptions. WILLDO: Finish up Unit Testing for PuzzleClass and Planet Class.

UPDATE: 11/14/2015 Kenny Cauthen Finished up PuzzleClassTester. Contains menu system that works and can test Puzzle attributes. Fixed some regex issue with the removeNonWords Method. Clean up some code and typos in GameController2 and PuzzleMaker. Created a no arg contructor for Puzzle. Spruced up the genericinputfailure method to become genericHelpOrInputFailure(). Just stick that in your ending else statement or final switch to catch Help inputs or invalid inputs.

UPDATE: 11/14/2015 Kenny Cauthen Tester Class PuzzleClassTester and PlanetClassTester is complete. Made a quick change for static issues in GameController2. Added initializing of planetArrayList when player starts new Game.

UPDATE: 11/15/2015 Kenny Cauthen Planet Selection Menu has been updated. Created randomPlanet Method to help select random planets. Need to add more planets to the arraylist so that I can test it better. Crew Selection still needs work but I updated Captain Class methods. Flagged unnecesary methods from Captain class.
UPDATE: 11/15/2015 Kenny Cauthen Fixed Planet Selection, Random Planets methods. Correctly gets planets based on having navigator or not.
